com.mojang.datafixers.optics.profunctors

Interface Cartesian<P extends K2,Mu extends Cartesian _>

  • Type Parameters:
    P - The transformation type.
    Mu - The witness type for this profunctor.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Mu<P>, Kind2 P, Profunctor P
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AffineP<P,Mu>, Mapping<P,Mu>, TraversalP<P,Mu>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Affine.Instance, Forget.Instance, ForgetOpt.Instance, FunctionType.Instance, Lens.Instance, ReForgetC.Instance, Traversal.Instance

    public interface Cartesian<P extends K2,Mu extends Cartesian _>
extends Profunctor P
    A profunctor that supports converting a transformation acting on some type to and from a transformation acting on pairs holding that type. This allows one to add a "pass-through" value to the type transformed via the profunctor that is left untransformed.
    Type Shape:
    %.Type. %0

    • Method Detail

      • first

        <A,B,C> P<(A,C),(B,C)> first(P<A,B> input)
        Converts the given transformation into one that transforms the first type of a Pair. The second type is not transformed - any values of that type are passed through the returned transformation unchanged.
        Type Parameters:
        A - The input type.
        B - The output type.
        C - A "pass-through" type that is not transformed.
        Parameters:
        input - The transformation.
        Returns:
        A transformation on pairs, where the first type is transformed and the second is not.

      • second

        default <A,B,C> P<(C,A),(C,B)> second(P<A,B> input)
        Converts the given transformation into one that transforms the second type of a Pair. The first type is not transformed - any values of that type are passed through the returned transformation unchanged.
        Implementation Requirements:
        The default implementation calls first(App2) and swaps the order of the types in the Pair.
        Type Parameters:
        A - The input type.
        B - The output type.
        C - A "pass-through" type that is not transformed.
        Parameters:
        input - The transformation.
        Returns:
        A transformation on pairs, where the second type is transformed and the first is not.

      • toFP2

        default FunctorProfunctor<CartesianLike _> P toFP2()
        Converts this profunctor into a FunctorProfunctor that distributes CartesianLike functors.
